#  AQI Simple Reflex Agent 

This project implements a Simple Reflex Agent that monitors air quality
in real-time.

The system collects environmental data from the World Air Quality Index
(WAQI) API and calculates the Air Quality Index (AQI) using Indian AQI
breakpoint formulas inside the program.

Instead of directly displaying AQI from the API, the agent: - Collects
pollutant values (PM2.5, PM10, NO2) - Calculates AQI using standard
formulas - Determines air quality category - Identifies the dominant
pollutant

This ensures that AQI measurement is done by our code logic.

 Agent Architecture-

Environment → Sensor → Rule Engine → Actuator
  
Environment----

Real-world air pollution data.

 Sensor-----

API call: https://api.waqi.info/feed/{city}/?token=API_KEY

 Rule Engine-----

Implements the AQI formula:

AQI = ((I_high - I_low) / (C_high - C_low)) \* (C - C_low) + I_low

The highest pollutant sub-index becomes the final AQI.

Actuator

Displays: - Pollutant concentrations - Sub-indices - Final AQI -
Category - Dominant pollutant

AQI Categories (India Standard)

0--50 → Good
51--100 → Satisfactory
101--200 → Moderate
201--300 → Poor
301--400 → Very Poor
401--500 → Severe


 How to Run

1.  Install required library: pip install requests

2.  Run the Python file: python aqi_agent.py

3.  Enter city name when prompted.

